text: Rakahanga is an electorate of the Cook Islands. It was created in 1964. Rakahanga is on the island of Rakahanga. ==Election results== While Tina Browne previously held Rakahanga as a member of the Democratic Party, she was made the member due to an electoral petition after Toka Hagai (a member of the Cook Islands Party) resigned. At the 2018 general election, Hagai gained the seat from Browne,. ==References== Category:Cook Islands electorates
title: Rakahanga (electorate)
